<div id="t4-main-body" class="t4-section  t4-main-body  container"><div class="t4-section-inner container-fluid"><div class="t4-row row"><div class="t4-col component col-12 col-md-6 col-lg container"><div id="system-message-container" aria-live="polite"></div><div class="com-content-article item-page" ><div class="page-header"><h1 > Accurate guide on Singapore nominee director (ACRA insights) </h1></div><div class="ja-share-button" layout="default" ></div><dl class="article-info text-muted"> <dt class="article-info-term"> Details </dt><dd class="createdby" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person"> Written by: <a href="../../../our-experts/author/overseas-company-formation-experts.html" >Experts in overseas company formation</a> </dd> <span style="display: none;" itemprop="publisher" itemscope> <span >Experts in overseas company formation</span> <span itemprop="logo" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject"> <img src="../../../../templates/ja_alpha/images/logo.png" alt="logo" width="160" height="40"> <meta itemprop="width" content="auto" /><meta itemprop="height" content="auto" /></span> </span> <dd class="modified"> <span class="fa fa-calendar" aria-hidden="true"></span> <time datetime="2025-07-10T16:02:55+07:00" itemprop="dateModified"> Last Updated: 10 July 2025	</time> </dd> </dl><ul class="fields-container"> <li class="field-entry country "> <span class="field-label ">Country: </span> <span class="field-value ">Singapore</span> </li> <li class="field-entry services "> <span class="field-label ">Services: </span> <span class="field-value ">Company formation</span> </li> <li class="field-entry rating-count "> <span class="field-label ">Rating Count: </span> <span class="field-value ">2</span> </li> <li class="field-entry rating-value "> <span class="field-label ">Rating Value: </span> <span class="field-value ">5</span> </li></ul><div class="com-content-article__body"><p>You are planning to set up a private limited in Singapore as a foreigner, everything seems fine until you start to write down yourself as the sole director of the company. Your application is unacceptable from that point forward.Â </p><p>The reason? To incorporate a company in Singapore, you need to appoint a local director for your Singapore private limited, and in this case, a Singapore nominee director.</p><p>So,Â </p><ul> <li>What is a Singapore nominee director?</li> <li>What are their responsibilities?Â </li> <li>What are the risks of hiring a local director?</li> <li>How can you appoint one for your local company in Singapore?</li> </ul><p>Â In this comprehensive guide, you will learn exactly everything you need to know about the Singapore nominee director.</p><p>Be sure to read to the end. We share accurate knowledge you need to know and what to expect with your nominee director.</p><p>Letâ€™s get started.</p><h2 class="indexed"><span id="what-is-a-nominee-director-in-singapore" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">1.</span> <span class="heading_text">What is a nominee director in Singapore?</span></h2><p>Based on the official ACRA Register of <a href="https://www.acra.gov.sg/docs/default-source/default-document-library/compliance/register-of-controllers/acra-guidance-on-register-of-nominee-directors-for-companies-(v1-7)-(4-oct).pdf?sfvrsn=4e3d06c9_2" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Nominee Director - Guidance for Companies</a>, Â the nominee director definition is as follows</p><blockquote><p>â€œ A director is a nominee if the director is accustomed or under an obligation whether formal or informal to act in accordance with the directions, instructions or wishes of any other personâ€</p></blockquote><p>According to the <a href="https://sso.agc.gov.sg/Act/CoA1967" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Singapore Companies Act section 145</a> the requirement for a director in Singapore is as follows:</p><p><img src="../../../../images/2025/07/singapore-companies-act-on-nominee-director.png" width="700" height="250" class="float-none" alt="Singapore Companies Acr on singapore director" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"></p><blockquote><p>"145.Â (1) Â Every company must have <strong>at least one director who is ordinarily resident in Singapore </strong>and, where the company only has one member, that sole director may also be the sole member of the company.<br>(2) Â No person other than <strong>a natural person</strong> who has attained<strong> the age of 18 years</strong> and who is otherwise<strong> of full legal capacity</strong> may be a director of a company."</p></blockquote><p>In simple terms, the Singapore Companies Act requires that all companies must have at least one director who is a Singapore citizen or a permanent resident in Singapore.Â </p><p>Â A nominee director in Singapore is <strong>a person officially hired as a director of a company but does not actively manage or control the business</strong>. They are often appointed to meet legal requirements, such as having a local director when setting up a company in Singapore.<strong></strong></p><p>The nominee acts on behalf of the actual owner or shareholders and has no real decision-making authority. However, they must still comply with Singapore's laws and regulations.</p><p>A nominee director is a direct solution for non-residents who do not have a trusted contact in Singapore.</p><p>For foreign individuals and foreign companies, this is the fastest, simplest way to satisfy the ACRA requirements and proceed with company incorporation, even if you have no personal ties or relocation plans.</p><h2 class="indexed"><span id="do-you-need-a-nominee-director-for-your-singapore-company" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">2.</span> <span class="heading_text">Do you need a nominee director for your Singapore company?</span></h2><p>A Singapore company must have at least one resident director. To be qualified as a local resident, the person must beÂ </p><ol> <li>Singapore citizen or Singapore permanent resident or</li> <li>Employment Pass holder, Entre Pass holder (This person must work for the same company of which he/she want to act as a director).</li> </ol><p>If you, your business partners, or investors do not live in Singapore, or if your company is a foreign entity expanding into Singapore, you will need a nominee director to fulfill regulatory obligations.</p><table border="1" style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100.047%; height: 156.75px;"><colgroup><col style="width: 49.9289%;"><col style="width: 49.9289%;"></colgroup> <tbody> <tr style="height: 20.7917px;"> <td style="height: 20.7917px;">Your situation</td> <td style="height: 20.7917px;">What to do</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 73.5833px;"> <td style="height: 73.5833px;">A foreigner or foreign entity incorporating a local company in Singapore</td> <td style="height: 73.5833px;"><ul> <li>Use nominee director service or;</li> <li>Find a local person to be your director</li> </ul> </td> </tr> <tr style="height: 20.7917px;"> <td style="height: 20.7917px;">Foreigners planning to relocate to Singapore</td> <td style="height: 20.7917px;"><ul> <li><span class="fabric-text-color-mark" data-text-custom-color="#bf2600">Find a nominee director and apply for an Employment Pass (EP) or Entre Pass</span></li> </ul> </td> </tr> <tr style="height: 20.7917px;"> <td style="height: 20.7917px;">Foreigners having an employment pass</td> <td style="height: 20.7917px;"><ul> <li>Don't need a nominee director, you can apply to be the sole director</li> <li>If you are applying, you need to temporarily use the nominee director service until you have <a href="singapore-employment-pass.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">an EP</a>.</li> </ul> </td> </tr> </tbody> </table><p></p><p>Remember that you need to appoint your nominee director<strong> within 6 months of company incorporation. Failure to do so will lead to legal penalties.</strong></p><div class="glac-article-box-cta"><div class="row"><div class="col-12 col-xl-7 d-flex flex-column justify-content-center"><p><strong>Reliable nominee director at your fingertips</strong></p><div class="glac-article-text-box-cta"><p>To be successful overseas is to find a reliable partner with whom you can count on for Singapore company formation and management.</p><p>Global Link Asia Consulting is proud to be the partner hundreds of entrepreneurs place their trust in.</p><p>Hundreds of business owners find peace of mind with our trusted nominee director service, and you can too.</p></div> <a class="t4b-btn bg-btn-gradient-1 glac-btn-callQR mobileCall" t4-type="t4b-btn" href="tel:+84938531588" t4-bid="core_element_basic_button" t4-group="Element" title="TÆ° váº¥n vá»›i chuyÃªn gia ngay" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#modalCall"><span id="i8lza">Book a call today!</span></a></div><div class="glac-article-img-box-cta col-12 col-xl-5 d-none d-xl-block"><img src="../../../../images/2023/07/tai-khoan-ngan-hang-singapore-uy-tin.jpg" width="350" height="350" loading="lazy"></div></div></div><p></p><p>Over 10 years of operations, we have successfully helped foreign entrepreneurs setupÂ  a presence in Singapore.</p><p>Here is a story of one of our clients, Anna, a German entrepreneur.Â </p><p>Anna wanted to launch an e-commerce platform in Singapore without moving there. With no local contacts, she engaged Global Link Asia Consulting for our nominee director service. We helped her to register the company and open a local bank account remotely.</p><h2 class="indexed"><span id="how-much-are-the-singapore-nominee-director-fees" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">3.</span> <span class="heading_text">How much are the Singapore nominee director fees?</span></h2><p>Nominee director fees in Singapore typically<strong> range from as low as SGD 800 to SGD 5,000 annually or more</strong>.</p><p>Extra costs may arise for certain services provided byÂ corporate service providers.</p><p>Corporate service providers require a security deposit to <strong>cover risks associated with Singapore nomineeÂ </strong><span style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;"><strong>directors</strong></span>.</p><p>They use it to address potential issues such asÂ <strong>company strike-offs, government fillings due to your action or your company misconduct.</strong></p><div class="glac-article-box-cta"><div class="row"><div class="col d-flex flex-column justify-content-center"><p class="glac-article-heading-box-cta">Our expert tip</p><div class="glac-article-text-box-cta"><p>Always check what is included in your providerâ€™s fee. Some fees cover only statutory duties, and others bundle additional compliance services (e.g., corporate secretarial support).</p></div></div></div></div><h2 class="indexed"><span id="why-do-you-need-to-have-a-nominee-director" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">4.</span> <span class="heading_text">Why do you need to have a nominee director?</span></h2><p>In addition to fulfilling residency rules under the Singapore Companies Act, having a nominee director is crucial for foreign owners due to the other 3 important reasons below:</p><div data-rlta-element="container" data-rlta-state="initial" data-rlta-id="1" data-rlta-type="accordions" data-rlta-title-tag="div" data-rlta-orientation="vertical" data-rlta-wrap-buttons="false" data-rlta-remember-active="false" data-rlta-theme="neutral" data-rlta-color-panels="false" data-rlta-positioning="top" data-rlta-alignment="left" data-rlta-has-button-scroller="false"><div id="rlta-1-to-work-with-the-singapore-authorities" role="button" aria-controls="rlta-panel-1-to-work-with-the-singapore-authorities" aria-expanded="true" tabindex="0" data-rlta-alias="1-to-work-with-the-singapore-authorities" data-rlta-element="button" data-rlta-state="open"><div data-rlta-element="heading"> 1. To work with the Singapore authorities</div></div><div id="rlta-panel-1-to-work-with-the-singapore-authorities" aria-labelledby="rlta-1-to-work-with-the-singapore-authorities" tabindex="-1" data-rlta-element="panel" data-rlta-state="open" data-rlta-color="false"><div data-rlta-element="panel-content"><p>The Singapore government <strong>requires a person who is physically present and can be contacted if the company violates any laws.Â </strong></p><p><strong>Â </strong>A local director plays a key role by performing necessary checks to ensure the company adheres to all legal requirements.</p><p>Although they do not manage the company, Singapore's Companies Act holds them to the same duties and liabilities as a regular director.</p></div></div><div id="rlta-2-to-maintain-the-privacy-of-the-actual-director-the-shareholder-who-is-in-control-of-the-company" role="button" aria-controls="rlta-panel-2-to-maintain-the-privacy-of-the-actual-director-the-shareholder-who-is-in-control-of-the-company" aria-expanded="false" tabindex="0" data-rlta-alias="2-to-maintain-the-privacy-of-the-actual-director-the-shareholder-who-is-in-control-of-the-company" data-rlta-element="button" data-rlta-state="closed"><div data-rlta-element="heading"> 2. To maintain the privacy of the actual director, the shareholder who is in control of the company.</div></div><div id="rlta-panel-2-to-maintain-the-privacy-of-the-actual-director-the-shareholder-who-is-in-control-of-the-company" aria-labelledby="rlta-2-to-maintain-the-privacy-of-the-actual-director-the-shareholder-who-is-in-control-of-the-company" tabindex="-1" hidden="true" data-rlta-element="panel" data-rlta-state="closed" data-rlta-color="false"><div data-rlta-element="panel-content"><p>To protect the identity of the true decision-maker, a company may appoint a nominee director.Â <br>In this arrangement, the <strong data-start="214" data-end="254">shareholder who controls the company</strong> stays behind the scenes, while the nominee appears in official records</p></div></div><div id="rlta-3-to-open-a-business-bank-accounts-in-singapore" role="button" aria-controls="rlta-panel-3-to-open-a-business-bank-accounts-in-singapore" aria-expanded="false" tabindex="0" data-rlta-alias="3-to-open-a-business-bank-accounts-in-singapore" data-rlta-element="button" data-rlta-state="closed"><div data-rlta-element="heading"> 3. To open a business bank accounts in Singapore</div></div><div id="rlta-panel-3-to-open-a-business-bank-accounts-in-singapore" aria-labelledby="rlta-3-to-open-a-business-bank-accounts-in-singapore" tabindex="-1" hidden="true" data-rlta-element="panel" data-rlta-state="closed" data-rlta-color="false"><div data-rlta-element="panel-content"><p>This local representation is also needed for opening corporate bank accounts, applying for business licenses, and responding to government queries or audits.</p><p>For many overseas founders, a nominee director unlocks access to critical services quickly and efficiently.</p><p>...</p></div></div></div><h2 class="indexed"><span id="what-are-the-roles-and-responsibilities-of-a-singapore-nominee-director" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">5.</span> <span class="heading_text">What are the roles and responsibilities of a Singapore nominee director?Â </span></h2><p>Even though the nominee director has no control over the company operations and management, they still have duties and responsibilities to uphold under the Singapore Companies Act.</p><p><strong>Legal compliance</strong></p><ul> <li>Â Oversee that the company adheres to all relevant laws, regulations, and statutory requirements;</li> <li>Stay updated on changes in laws that may impact the company's operations;</li> <li>Maintain accurate records and help submit required documents to regulatory authorities on time.</li> </ul><p><strong>Fiduciary responsibility</strong></p><ul> <li>Maintain confidentiality Â of all involved parties to protect the company secrets;</li> <li>Make decisions that consider the interests of the appointer while complying with Singaporeâ€™s laws;</li> <li>Act with honesty and professionalism in all dealings.</li> </ul><p><strong>Fulfillment in legal requirements</strong></p><ul> <li>Meet the legal requirement for a Singapore company to have at least one resident director.</li> </ul><p data-pm-slice="1 1 []">H<span class="fabric-text-color-mark" data-text-custom-color="#bf2600">ere is a simple table showing the role and responsibilities between you as the company founder and director and the nominee director:</span></p><table border="1" style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100.004%;"><colgroup><col style="width: 50%;"><col style="width: 50%;"></colgroup> <tbody> <tr> <td>Questions</td> <td>Answer</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Who acts as the executive director of the Singapore company?</td> <td>You</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Who signs the contractual and financial documents?</td> <td>You</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Is the nominee director involved in the company matter other than to satisfy his/her legal compliance, the fiduciary duties?</td> <td>No</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Can the nominee director review and scrutinize the bank statement?</td> <td>Yes, nominee directors can do it to fulfill their fiduciary duties</td> </tr> </tbody> </table><p>Breaking the director's duties (No matter what your role is: nominee director or an executive director) can have serious consequences, both in civil court and in criminal court. The punishment depends on the severity of the offense.Â </p><ol> <li>For minor offenses, a director might have to pay a fine of up to S$5,000 or go to jail for up to two years.Â </li> <li>More serious offenses could lead to a five-year ban from being a director</li> </ol><p>That is why, trustworthy providers conduct strict KYC and require indemnity agreements for all foreign clients if they need to use a nominee director service.</p><h2 class="indexed"><span id="is-there-any-difference-between-a-nominee-director-a-company-director-and-a-nominee-shareholder" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">6.</span> <span class="heading_text">Is there any difference between a nominee director, a company director, and a nominee shareholder?</span></h2><p>Here is a table outlining the primary difference between a nominee director, a company director, and a nominee shareholder. Knowing this key difference allows you to understand more about the roles and responsibilities of a nominee director.</p><table border="1" style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100.034%; height: 395.091px;"><colgroup><col style="width: 25.0323%;"><col style="width: 25.0323%;"><col style="width: 25.0323%;"><col style="width: 25.0323%;"></colgroup> <thead> <tr style="height: 20.7943px;"> <td style="height: 20.7943px;">Aspect</td> <td style="height: 20.7943px;">Nominee Director</td> <td style="height: 20.7943px;">Company Director</td> <td style="height: 20.7943px;">Nominee Shareholder</td> </tr> </thead> <tbody> <tr style="height: 62.3828px;"> <td style="height: 62.3828px;">Definition</td> <td style="height: 62.3828px;">An individual appointed to meet legal requirements but with no real control over company operations.</td> <td style="height: 62.3828px;">An individual with legal authority and responsibility for managing the company.</td> <td style="height: 62.3828px;">An individual or entity that holds shares on behalf of the actual owner.</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 41.5885px;"> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">Role</td> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">Fulfill the statutory requirement of having a local resident director.</td> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">Oversee and manage the company's day-to-day operations and strategic direction.</td> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">Act as a proxy for the actual shareholder.</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 62.3828px;"> <td style="height: 62.3828px;">Responsibilities</td> <td style="height: 62.3828px;"><span>Compliance, statutory duties only.</span></td> <td style="height: 62.3828px;">Operations, compliance, strategy.</td> <td style="height: 62.3828px;">Vote/shares as instructed.</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 41.5885px;"> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">Control</td> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">Limited to statutory and compliance duties; no actual control over business operations.</td> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">Full control over company operations and decision-making processes.</td> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">No control over the company; acts as a proxy for the beneficial owner.</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 41.5885px;"> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">Legal Liability</td> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">Legal liability for the companyâ€™s non-compliance and unlawful acts.</td> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">Full legal liability for the companyâ€™s actions and decisions.</td> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">Minimal legal liability, primarily to ensure shares are held as per instructions.</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 41.5885px;"> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">Appointment Purpose</td> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">To meet statutory requirements for local residency.</td> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">To provide leadership, strategic direction, and management.</td> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">To protect the identity of the actual shareholder and hold shares in trust.</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 41.5885px;"> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">Appointment Process</td> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">Appointed to fulfill legal requirements, often by a service provider.</td> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">Appointed by shareholders or the board of directors based on qualifications</td> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">Appointed by the beneficial owner to hold shares on their behalf.</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 41.5885px;"> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">Remuneration</td> <td style="height: 41.5885px;"><p>Typically receives a fee for acting as a nominee director</p></td> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">Receives salary, bonuses, and other compensation for their role.</td> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">Receive a nominal fee for acting as a nominee.</td> </tr> </tbody> </table><p></p><h2 class="indexed"><span id="who-can-be-a-nominee-director-what-are-the-eligibility-criteria" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">7.</span> <span class="heading_text">Who can be a nominee director? What are the eligibility criteria?</span></h2><p>Not everyone can be a nominee director for your Singapore company. They need to satisfy the eligibility criteria set by the Singapore government.Â </p><p>Based on the <a href="https://www.acra.gov.sg/how-to-guides/setting-up-a-local-company/appointing-directors-company-secretary-and-other-key-personnel" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ACRA Appointing Directors section</a>, the eligibility criteria are as follows</p><h3 class="indexed"><span id="for-a-foreigner-wanting-to-hire-a-nominee-director" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">7.1.</span> <span class="heading_text">For a foreigner wanting to hire a nominee director</span></h3><p>There are 3 most important criteria to become a legitimate nominee director, which are <strong>the age requirement (at least 18 years old), Â no criminal records, and Singapore citizenship or permanent residency.</strong></p><table border="1" style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100.034%; height: 83.1771px;"><colgroup><col style="width: 49.9834%;"><col style="width: 49.9834%;"></colgroup> <tbody> <tr style="height: 41.5885px;"> <td style="height: 41.5885px;">Age Requirement</td> <td style="height: 41.5885px;"><ul> <li>Be at least 18 years old and of full legal capacity</li> </ul> </td> </tr> <tr style="height: 20.7943px;"> <td style="height: 20.7943px;">Singapore Citizenship or Permanent Residency</td> <td style="height: 20.7943px;"><ul> <li>Be a citizen or permanent resident of Singapore and have a permanent address in Singapore.</li> <li>Be a natural person (A company as a director is not allowed to be a nominee director,</li> </ul> </td> </tr> <tr style="height: 20.7943px;"> <td style="height: 20.7943px;">No criminal record</td> <td style="height: 20.7943px;"><ul> <li>Have a clean criminal record as proof of credibility and trustworthiness.</li> <li>Have no history of being disqualified from holding a director position.</li> </ul><p>If you are looking for someone to be your local director, you must consider this criterion carefully to avoid fraudulent or dishonest activities in the future.</p></td> </tr> </tbody> </table><p></p><div class="glac-article-box-cta"><div class="row"><div class="col d-flex flex-column justify-content-center"><p class="glac-article-heading-box-cta">You don't need to use a nominee director service with this tip</p><div class="glac-article-text-box-cta"><p>If you want to find a local director for the company, you should first check if you have any reliable connection in Singapore that can be one. They can be your cousins, your families, your friends, your working partners.Â </p><p>As long as they are trustworthy, meet listed requirements, and you build a sustainable business, there is nothing to worry about</p></div></div></div></div><h3 class="indexed"><span id="for-foreigners-wanting-to-be-a-sole-director" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">7.2.</span> <span class="heading_text">For foreigners wanting to be a sole director</span></h3><p>One solution many foreign entrepreneurs have successfully done is to apply for a work pass such as an Employment Pass, Entrepreneur Pass, or One Pass.Â </p><p>This would make you a resident of Singapore so you can be a director of the company. Â However, bear in mind that it is complicated to get government approval.</p><p>In addition, you still need to fulfill other criteria listed above in the For a Singapore resident: At least 18 years old with full legal capacity, no criminal record, and no disqualification from acting as a director of a company.</p><h2 class="indexed"><span id="employment-pass-or-nominee-director-which-one-to-choose" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">8.</span> <span class="heading_text">Employment Pass or Nominee director, which one to choose?</span></h2><p>Often, you donâ€™t know which solution is the right solution:Â  Employment pass or nominee director</p><p>Here is an overview of the 5 solutions with scenarios for satisfying the local directorâ€™s requirement. The right solution is the one that fits your plan and needs.</p><p>Use this quick comparison to decide:</p><table border="1" style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 235.172px;"><colgroup><col style="width: 16.6873%;"><col style="width: 16.6873%;"><col style="width: 16.6873%;"><col style="width: 16.6873%;"><col style="width: 16.6873%;"><col style="width: 16.6873%;"></colgroup> <tbody> <tr style="height: 20.7969px;"> <td style="height: 20.7969px;">Option</td> <td style="height: 20.7969px;">When to choose</td> <td style="height: 20.7969px;">Control</td> <td style="height: 20.7969px;">Initial speed</td> <td style="height: 20.7969px;">Cost</td> <td style="height: 20.7969px;">Best for</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 110.391px;"> <td style="height: 110.391px;">Nominee director</td> <td style="height: 110.391px;"><p>No plans to relocate</p><p>No local contact</p></td> <td style="height: 110.391px;">High</td> <td style="height: 110.391px;">Immediate</td> <td style="height: 110.391px;">Annual fee</td> <td style="height: 110.391px;">Remote founders</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 62.3906px;"> <td style="height: 62.3906px;">Employment Pass</td> <td style="height: 62.3906px;">Move to Singapore and manage directly</td> <td style="height: 62.3906px;">Full</td> <td style="height: 62.3906px;">2-6 weeks for the pass</td> <td style="height: 62.3906px;">2-3 year fee for renewal</td> <td style="height: 62.3906px;">Owners seeking to relocate</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 41.5938px;"> <td style="height: 41.5938px;">EP + Nominee Director</td> <td style="height: 41.5938px;">Immediate setup, then relocate later</td> <td style="height: 41.5938px;">Full (after EP approved)</td> <td style="height: 41.5938px;">Immediate</td> <td style="height: 41.